cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with the problem of neural association and memory in a network of non-binary neurons. This falls under the broad category of neural networks and machine learning, which is covered by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of linear algebraic structures and eigenvalues, which are topics covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The iterative learning algorithm and neural update algorithms are related to information theory and signal processing, which are covered by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing). Finally, the paper uses simulations to validate the proposed methods, which falls under the category of data science and simulation, covered by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
